The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, June 11, 2003 				 Atal invites Sonia
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, June 10: Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee has invited Congress president Sonia Gandhi for a briefing on the Iraq developments on Sunday. 																								According to official sources, the issue of whether India should send its troops to Iraq could figure in the briefing.																								The interaction would be part of the process of consultation on Iraq the government plans to have with the Opposition. 																								To begin with, however, Vajpayee has asked only the main Opposition party over.
